{"title":"Crisis Renal Esclerodermica","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Nefrología/Crisis Renal Esclerodermica-2024-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Crisis Renal\\NEsclerodermica","guid":"OMhvp7gJ9ONIPUrsDayz6w","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Caso clínico ","guid":"49Q8BddDwhxjg2cruAHJxA","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"- Información\\Ndel Paciente","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"- Edad: 58 años","guid":"CIwO0pAKGn3As_q_Mg0feg","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"- Sexo: Femenino","guid":"nFVb3ATlBb8_khgvR4znsw","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"- Antecedentes relevantes: Esclerosis sistémica diagnosticada hace 10 años","guid":"zLwzsSWqx5QPQYFRA7CawQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"- Motivo de Consulta","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"- Presenta aumento progresivo de creatinina sérica y presión arterial elevada","guid":"OD-n7_EKITFGExlWHpvvdg","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"- Examen Físico","guid":"GotPF2I3pCi3aclHe6nIQg","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"- PA: 180/110 mmHg","guid":"IQPex-5tDVl263dpI0l_AA","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"- Edema en miembros inferiores","guid":"um7Ag199FoFZJ6pPgzppbA","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"8","text":"- Piel endurecida y brillante en manos y cara","guid":"2MB2WvN_RdaLqYIEBWVqww","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"1","text":"- Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"- Creatinina: 2.8 mg/dL (incremento desde 0.9 mg/dL en 6 meses)","guid":"3kg78slj4yCpa42fbp642A","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"- Proteinuria: 2 g en 24 horas","guid":"zRp5HaCEwTYQIpH9gJZc-A","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"12","text":"- Hematuria: 30-50 hematíes por campo de gran aumento","guid":"ktAU4Wgz9DT3zEerVILHdw","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"- ANA positivo, anticentromero positivo","guid":"1zdczIo8TMMWowWHymqcaA","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"1","text":"- Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"- Crisis renal esclerodérmica, caracterizada por vasculopatía renal, fibrosis y autoinmunidad.","guid":"NVLjDDgKImh-EDYH6uv6PA","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"Definición basada en la presencia de FSR reducido y activación del SRAA","guid":"D1idklwGKz4QAevmazoB5w","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"1","text":"- Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"- Inhibidores de la ECA como pilar del tratamiento, esenciales para manejar la PA y prevenir daño renal adicional","guid":"xyeBUcg0mkfmDNMTlkuCpw","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"- Corticosteroides a dosis bajas para controlar la inflamación sistémica","guid":"1VXXo1KbMThodEHsxTSB7g","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"- Consideración de diálisis debido al nivel elevado de creatinina, con un porcentaje de pacientes que requieren diálisis permanente aún con tratamiento","guid":"zx1xo46LHlK25qogoVcflg","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"1","text":"- Monitorización por posible necesidad de trasplante renal, dadas las mejores tasas de sobrevida comparado con diálisis","guid":"fFalWSQkIpvQq1uxU_g61w","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"0","text":"Perlas","guid":"bccjrzaUCj16jmWes4uZ9A","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"Complicación renal más seria de la ES: Crisis renal de la esclerodermia (CRE) (8,10,11)","guid":"6CRdpt48wWDH5Xg27slOKw","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"Porcentaje de pacientes con ES difusa cutánea que desarrollan CRE: 5-20% (3,8)","guid":"9e290e9Wr-_UtFeoBxnxRw","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"25","text":"Principales factores de riesgo para CRE: Enfermedad cutánea difusa y rápidamente\\Nprogresiva, glucocorticoides a altas dosis, ac. anti-RNA polimerasa III (15,19,21)","guid":"sn7_EUuCiaYhw7DqgpTd2w","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"25","text":"Pilar del tratamiento de la CRE: Inhibidores de la enzima convertidora de angiotensina (iECA) (41)","guid":"7PsD4qAl4htLzIoyAbwEMQ","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"25","text":"Porcentaje de pacientes con CRE que requieren diálisis permanente a pesar del tratamiento con iECA: 19-40% (7)","guid":"kObrLb_fmKh_pbJ0lwRIOw","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"0","text":"Definición","guid":"kugwM2vCtb0_ODI_3WbCwg","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"Complicación de la ES con vasculopatía renal, fibrosis y autoinmunidad → ⬇ FSR → activación del SRAA\\N→ crisis hipertensiva, injuria renal aguda (IRA) y microangiopatía trombótica (MAT) (17,18)","guid":"NNvIgf8HlWfyxFZddLUMTA","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatología","guid":"DUQvR1rewF26cJ1d1oEwzA","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"Individuos susceptibles con ES tienen alteraciones renales: vasculopatía con\\Nproliferación y engrosamiento intimal → ⬇ FSR, fibrosis intersticial, autoinmunidad","guid":"hw5BftzizTlofzMI_IZL2w","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"Gatillante (no definido) → daño endotelial → liberación de citoquinas y factores de crecimiento → vasculopatía\\Nproliferativa de músculo liso → isquemia glomerular y activación sostenida del SRAA → CRE (18)","guid":"bjfL7BdFRlTB3Qx_b2OitQ","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"33","text":"Endotelina-1 y sus receptores A y B aumentados en CRE → ⬇ FSR (31-33)","guid":"uSZLUmkTC4dzzNCx9PpZlQ","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"33","text":"Complemento: Aumento de C5b-9 y actividad de vía alterna en CRE. Potencial objetivo terapéutico (eculizumab) (26,27)","guid":"R230n23TSvZk-dspj14paA","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"9u_dZU4g3o-0o5bL0105Pw","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"Incidencia de CRE: 5-20% en ES cutánea difusa vs 1-2% en ES cutánea limitada (8,9)","guid":"yNC_ucICPBbx-NTz8SQZKQ","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"Mayor incidencia en USA, UK y Australia. Menor en Japón (1-3%) (9,12,13)","guid":"PqMXwUtRmLU_fcrrDEvqkQ","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"Distribución por sexo similar a ES en general (3:1 F:M) (15)","guid":"XmMPCpaI9Uyt7kBi4tNz2w","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"38","text":"Complicación temprana, 75% ocurre en los primeros 4-5 años de enfermedad (50)","guid":"_cghVFG_8HJnJXhjyOFM5Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"0","text":"Factores de riesgo\\N(15,50-53)","guid":"aN26JqPPsskSMWeq78ewlA","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"Enfermedad cutánea difusa rápidamente progresiva (OR 2.05, IC 95% 1.10-3.85) (16)","guid":"C7WOfjs2dJ5FG2qBZBW8pA","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"43","text":"Glucocorticoides a dosis >15 mg/día prednisona (OR 4.37, IC 95% 2.03-9.43) (21)","guid":"x7sEEenKVqKkr6-JsYQT9w","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"43","text":"Ac. anti-RNA polimerasa III (OR 5. 86, IC 95% 2.6-13.2) (15)","guid":"Be0-QRjV6jbcJrc5JDgZPw","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"43","text":"Frotes tendinosos palpables (OR 2.33, IC 95% 1.03-6.19) (17,50)","guid":"_ZIQPFxK_bGfFxsAktqHpg","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"43","text":"Anemia, derrame pericárdico, falla cardiaca congestiva (51,53)","guid":"lh7X_12tENIXeWpsfh4YeA","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"43","text":"Proteinuria (OR 5.55, IC 95% 3.4-8.9) (15)","guid":"PWRNuoZosV9IVd5odvmTzQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"0","text":"Clínica","guid":"9rvoS8YbZdXSIo8eohpOiw","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"Inicio abrupto de HTA moderada-severa, a veces con retinopatía y encefalopatía hipertensiva (23,31)","guid":"f1mmbjFBzfUGdb2xCDFlIA","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"Presión arterial media 178/102 mmHg (31)","guid":"hFJb6XkMBULcEtj_0Z5I8A","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"~10% son normotensos pero con ⬆ significativa vs basal (19)","guid":"j32cvdotNIGgw-yblxYqvw","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"50","text":"IRA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"50","text":"Sedimento urinario normal, sin proteinuria significativa","guid":"_oa_0ueoB97PJ1_AVjMx3w","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"50","text":"Signos de MAT: anemia hemolítica microangiopática, trombocitopenia, ⬆ LDH, ⬇ haptoglobina, esquistocitos","guid":"NgOEk2YL9sb6IjG1W7EHgw","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"50","text":"Otros: falla cardiaca, derrame pericárdico, cefalea, convulsiones","guid":"mPw8qFV4laxCm_DEZLLSVw","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"0","text":"Estudio","guid":"XAtcBQTvEBEEBYNDzOUEJA","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"Hemograma completo, frotis sangre periférica","guid":"fKO6OHQhID2bZz7M-6UStA","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"Creatinina, nitrógeno ureico, electrolitos plasmáticos","guid":"7W9xSIxPhZB1rjmKrjW8qg","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"58","text":"LDH, haptoglobina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"58","text":"Sedimento urinario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"58","text":"Si se sospecha otra MAT (PTT, SUH) además de CRE: Actividad ADAMTS13, toxina Shiga, complemento (27)","guid":"iY4HeFUDVBFXynzf3gmGug","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"ZVBiuk2hCP_xJPBuvNB4sA","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"Clínico en base a (8):","guid":"z7asy-FuM-_DVOv5w47jpA","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"IRA no explicada por otra causa, ⬆ aguda PA ≥140/90 mmHg o ⬆ ≥30 mmHg sistólica o ≥20\\NmmHg diastólica vs basal, en pacientes de alto riesgo (ac. anti-RNA pol III, enf. cutánea difusa,\\NGC recientes), considerar MAT, disfunción de órgano blanco o histología renal característica","guid":"a2X1v62yPefz8gQaiBeNDg","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"Biopsia renal generalmente no necesaria, pero puede descartar otros diagnósticos y entregar información pronóstica (47)","guid":"oA7dwLpgZzuOH5m1nqbO6Q","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"64","text":"Hallazgos: Proliferación y engrosamiento intimal en arterias arqueadas e interlobulillares. Aspecto 'piel de cebolla'. Isquemia glomerular. Fibrosis intersticial. (ver imagen 2)","guid":"6RLrzRRNdyuHIHZAE7DmQA","children":[]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico\\Ndiferencial","guid":"BpkfQW7eAYa2NH_UgzDZFw","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"Otras causas de IRA en ES: Prerrenal (falla cardiaca, hipovolemia), AINES, diuréticos (3)","guid":"WaF_97AGzo0emKlrr-h7Dw","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"Otras MAT: PTT, SUH, hipertensión maligna, rechazo crónico de trasplante, SAF (22)","guid":"yl6l4YKvhb0OexyWZb8kpw","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"69","text":"Vasculitis ANCA (+) con glomerulonefritis crescéntica pauciinmune (54,55)","guid":"Jz98qR_SUotCvLCbOr_L8A","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"RlaEtEMppTc9AC-S7Fc4RQ","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Objetivo: Normalizar PA a valores basales en 72 hrs (56)","guid":"U_9z7WUZ_pliJ9S90EE0Rw","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"1era línea: iECA. Titular rápidamente a dosis máxima (41)","guid":"cs5JOF8zO9UzG24VjIw6Lw","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"No suspender por ⬆ de creatinina, es esperable","guid":"dWXPKbKnEgYhw1ywJ6r8Cg","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"Continuar de por vida, incluso en diálisis","guid":"da6r4WN1dyBG8l3R7Vrw2g","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"73","text":"Si PA no controlada, agregar: Bloqueadores de canales de Ca, α-bloqueadores (56)","guid":"pxPLSHOwR9ORWxTPxLhmCg","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"73","text":"Evitar β-bloqueadores por riesgo de ⬇ gasto cardiaco y ⬆ vasoconstricción","guid":"RApX-7WieSdwA2NCAbLSFg","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"73","text":"Diálisis en 60%, inicialmente con HF, luego HD o PD (11)","guid":"ztjIS0bK1AfvvZ0HSc_nxg","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"73","text":"Considerar plasmaféresis si sospecha PTT concomitante (62)","guid":"SuHmkfxNiIJdtLLvrrO4KA","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"73","text":"Considerar eculizumab en casos refractarios con evidencia de activación del complemento (27)","guid":"ttEsUXoiaTAMBpek25dUjA","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"0","text":"Seguimiento y\\Npronóstico","guid":"o9AMip5NhfYSCY2vOFG3ew","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Monitorizar PA, creatinina y electrolitos plasmáticos, hemograma y signos de hemólisis (56)","guid":"gu-Wl_1WQZ0JDpvNZ7Q5aQ","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"Mortalidad 36% y 25% en diálisis permanente al año a pesar de iECA (7)","guid":"db352QLYQR5aFP2xS31K5Q","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"83","text":"Recuperación de función renal posible hasta 18-24 meses post inicio (8,31)","guid":"oIRvlKYUbxpMvts9KFRAvA","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"83","text":"Posibilidad de trasplante renal, con mejor sobrevida vs diálisis (91% vs 56% a 1 año) (7,51)","guid":"pTusSlfLa3-LVCvkV0s8RQ","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"83","text":"Recurrencia de CRE 2-9% (7,28)","guid":"3KJUAXb9d8KOmDaitm_6hQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"0","text":"Prevención","guid":"QgxJzT1PolSMKziggpQ0jg","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"No hay medidas preventivas establecidas más allá de reconocer y monitorizar pacientes de riesgo","guid":"zYHEnbrn9KW-EuI2g9A53A","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"Uso de iECA profilácticos es controversial y no se recomienda de rutina (35,55)","guid":"NalOeVVEP82qwy_wZcyrMg","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"Evitar GC en dosis >15 mg/d prednisona en ES difusa temprana (21)","guid":"rmk070lFxh1vaeUQGnsppg","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"m0gwqATWvUyQWkGR5oZ5yg","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Auspitz H, Wien Med Wochenschr 1863;13:739-41.","guid":"9ZMFywEeffKqfrlUwaVYbw","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"Steen VD, J Rheumatol 2005; 32:649.","guid":"2QEEFO5NLx4oAY6nVeoNdQ","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"Moore HC, Lancet 1952;262:68-80.","guid":"rGJ__5aquX5a5HqOyzLZJw","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"93","text":"Kim H, J Scleroderma Relat Disord 2020;6:21-36.","guid":"v0B6e462b9HhpQUIAAvTvA","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"93","text":"Penn H, QJM 2007;100:485-94.","guid":"s4qMcMbgxg-rhPNWeHGjEg","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"93","text":"Turk M, J Rheumatol 2016;43:1350-5.","guid":"wl0P8tMTJ0laJeMTnqldmA","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"93","text":"Denton CP, Best Pract Res Clin Rheum 2004;18:271-90.","guid":"1B3ibQR_1djM-XDpELbcsw","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"93","text":"Steen VD, Ann Intern Med 2000;133:600.","guid":"TecZbEgg0YMZwWCB2WIr_Q","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"93","text":"Hashimoto A, J Rheumatol 2011; 38:1931-9.","guid":"utmm_X5tipOr1L54Mcpeyg","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"93","text":"Nishimagi E, J Rheumatol 2007; 34:2050-5.","guid":"JvbEtiqM7FM_t8WfPQxgrw","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"93","text":"Moinzadeh P, J Rheumatol 2020; 47:241-8.","guid":"E9SH62yjYOoLEsRjzXgYFg","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"93","text":"DeMarco PJ, Arthritis Rheum 2002;46:2983-9.","guid":"oWlIlBc7h1ILQp7I4DGEZA","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"93","text":"Doré A, Arthritis Care Res 2013;65:1385.","guid":"8kYHIyuX0ENaIpXRGOeIXw","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"93","text":"Denton CP, Rheumatology 2009; 48:iii32-5.","guid":"-5AH5PSWlESUa8wAQXgocA","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"93","text":"Helfrich DJ, Arthritis Rheum 1989;32:1128.","guid":"Dog6y4wHdw8yUOcBTHmtPA","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"93","text":"Steen VD, Arthritis Rheum 1998;41:1613.","guid":"85YFJr3cItdMFiIh5lqyyw","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"93","text":"Batal I, Int J Rheumatol 2010;2010:543704.","guid":"7xAOcnXqO8spLQZv7Q0tEQ","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"93","text":"Guillevin L, Rheumatology 2012; 51:460.","guid":"-gCor5OmcqArsqN2R9IFmA","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"93","text":"Cavero T, Nephrol Dial Transplant 2017;32:466-74.","guid":"HS5U3ZJdLWHkwwjhUPTztw","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"93","text":"Uriarte MH, Case Rep Nephrol 2018;2018:6051083.","guid":"sAouX1SlR3npMh-Eh6d4LQ","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"93","text":"Pham PT, Am J Transplant 2005; 5:2565.","guid":"ILjDApWhTJVCY9Fkd6Rkjg","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"93","text":"Steen VD, Ann Intern Med 1990;113:352-7.","guid":"ZVKPYK7iXsNFqU5ruLR_aQ","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"93","text":"Steen VD, Medicine 1990;62:335.","guid":"5TAf6etkjY9puzDvX99N1w","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"93","text":"Batal I, Hum Pathol 2009;40:332.","guid":"8eAPy4VCZaOwKj-WxKZG1g","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"93","text":"Avouac J, Ann Rheum Dis 2016;75:103-9.","guid":"vodd03Ji8aJI1Ra5supOiw","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"93","text":"Steen VD, Am J Med 1984;76:779-86.","guid":"e4-COUsn6d73GhwAtt_8Cg","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"93","text":"DeMarco PJ, Arthritis Rheum 2002;46:2983-9.","guid":"mLMScZDDFXKqp7aaP8i-ww","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"93","text":"Arnaud L, Clin Nephrol 2007;68:165.","guid":"oh84pTucz8ooWux8AwHw5w","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"93","text":"Hudson M, Semin Arthritis Rheum 2014;43:666-72.","guid":"-cf_8wCyYRjjdTrhsOpDkw","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"93","text":"Lynch BM, Clin Exp Rheumatol 2016;34:106-9.","guid":"uiLnHwp1vTyVW0UR3mt5qQ","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"93","text":"Lian EC, Semin Thromb Hemost 2005;31:625-32. fig1.","guid":"RcZcQYDW2oPEorsIjD96hg","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"93","text":"Penn H, QJM 2007; 100:485-94. fig2.","guid":"nPNuzPv4JE6w2s5VOa6l0w","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"93","text":"Batal I, Int J Rheumatol 2010;2010:543704.","guid":"Dnt8lfpAw5H5ClYQ-Rb0WA","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":126,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Nefrología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Nefrología","filename":"Crisis Renal Esclerodermica-2024-1","id":"map_1301","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Crisis Renal Esclerodermica-2024-1"}